Look at the meta-kudo's obmc-console file. 
Multi-console is supported and there is no need to manually remove the configs from base recipe and other customization being done here.
Just need to use the OBMC_CONSOLE_TTYS variable with space separated tty ports and it will be properly handled.

https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-fii/meta-kudo/recipes-phosphor/console/obmc-console_%25.bbappend

Instead of changing this service file, can you create a new service, "host_console_uart_config.service" and in that service file, add the "RequiredBy=obmc-console@%i.service"

So this will avoid the need to modify the service file created by the obmc-console.
Done, RequiredBy=multi-user.target same as obmc-console@.service

this service is not needed by multi-user target. this is needed by obmc-console (or) must be run before host starts. so console server captures all log. 
Change this to "Before" obmc console service or the host power control service.

do we need this or can the upstream service is enough?
If we remove obmc-console@.service, we also remove multi-user.target which causes an issue as without it we cannot connect to Mpro or Host. We tested without the obmc-console@.service and it failed.
